cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories due to its focus on fingerprint presentation attack detection using deep neural networks. The use of laser speckle contrast imaging (LSCI) also suggests a potential fit for the multimedia (cs.MM) and image retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the use of deep neural networks for classification makes the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category a possible fit as well.
